claim.claim-text:
20. A method for controlling a mobile device, which provides a dual mode of a first mode and a second mode, the method comprising:
providing a first unlock interface to unlock a first lock state, wherein the first unlock interface allows the mobile device to enter into the first mode or the second mode after unlocking the first lock state;
displaying at least one application executed in the first mode when the mobile device enters into the first mode through the first unlock interface;
detecting an event for the second mode in the first mode;
entering a second lock state; and
providing a second unlock interface to unlock the second lock state, wherein the second unlock interface allows the mobile device to enter into only the second mode after unlocking the second lock state.
